  "texts": [
    "This approach allowed us to condense both spatial and temporal information within the prepared data.",
    "The voxel representations in a sub-recording are inputted to the networks sequentially as a time series, which are expected to regress the coordinates while considering the temporal dependency between adjacent voxel representations.",
    "Besides, the annotated data was divided into training and validation sets sub-sequently.",
    "Notably, we refrained from incorporating any extra data beyond the original one but decreased the default train stride from 15 to 5, which means the next subrecording will start 250us after the current one instead of 750us, in order to generate more data for training from the raw recordings.",
    "For the training process, we employed a single RTX 3090 Ti GPU."
  ],
